OL,3,CO'Neill offers apology for 'all lives
OL,4,Clost during conflict'
OL,6,F"I am sorry for all the lives lost
OL,7,Fduring the conflict, without exception.
OL,9,F"Regrettably the past cannot be
OL,10,Fchanged or be undone. Neither can the
OL,11,Fsuffering, the hurt or the political
OL,12,Fviolence or conflict be disowned by
OL,13,Frepublicans or by any other party to
OL,14,Fthe conflict.
OL,16,F"People's lives from every section of
OL,17,Fthe community were trespassed upon
OL,18,Fduring the conflict by British state
OL,19,Fforces, republicans, loyalists and
OL,20,Funimaginable grief, hurt, pain and
OL,21,Floss was inflicted."
