OL,3,CO'Neill offers apology for 'all lives
OL,4,Clost during conflict'
OL,6,F"It was a courageous role undertaken
OL,7,Fby people who wanted to defeat
OL,8,Fterrorism, protect the entire
OL,9,Fcommunity, and secure peace for us
OL,10,Fall. Whilst some will want to rewrite
OL,11,Fhistory and develop their own
OL,12,Fnarrative of the past which blames
OL,13,Fthose who tried to uphold the law as
OL,14,Fmuch as the terrorists, this is a
OL,15,Fdistortion of reality.
OL,17,F"90% of the deaths in the Troubles
OL,18,Fwere perpetrated by terrorists. We
OL,19,Fmust remember that the soldiers were
OL,20,Fon our streets because of the
OL,21,Fterrorist campaign.
