OL,3,CO'Neill offers apology for 'all lives
OL,4,Clost during conflict'
OL,6,F"In the coming days, we will be asking
OL,7,Fmore questions of those tasked with
OL,8,Fmaking decisions about Troubles
OL,9,Frelated prosecutions in Northern
OL,10,FIreland. Where evidence exists against
OL,11,Fterrorist perpetrators, innocent
OL,12,Fvictims must not be denied access to
OL,13,Fjustice. This principle cannot be
OL,14,Fcompromised."
OL,16,FDowning Street said it would not
OL,17,Fcomment on the report published by
OL,18,FOperation Kenova until the inquiry had
OL,19,Fcompleted its work.
